SIMPLE: semidiurnal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semidiurnal
<hw>Sem`i*di*ur"nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to, or accomplished in, half a day, or twelve hours;
occurring twice every day.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or traversed in, six hours, or in
half the time between the rising and setting of a heavenly body; <as>as,
a <ex>semidiurnal</ex> arc</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semidome</ent>⟦br⟧
